IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: FIRST CARE CLINIC IS A FEDERALLY QUALIFIED HEALTH CENTER PROVIDING MEDICAL, BEHAVIORAL HEALTH AND DENTAL SERVICES TO ALL, INCLUDING THE UNINSURED.
IRS990.MissionDesc: TO BE THE REGION'S PREMIER MEDICAL HOME DEDICATED TO PROVIDING ACCESS TO COMPASSIONATE, QUALITY CARE FOR ALL.
IRS990.Desc: PRIMARY MEDICAL CARE - FIRST CARE CLINIC, INC. CONTINUED OPERATIONS IN A PRIMARY CARE MEDICAL CLINIC. MEDICAL SERVICES INCLUDE: NON-EMERGENCY PRIMARY CARE, BEHAVIORAL HEALTH, PAP SMEARS, IMMUNIZATIONS, REFERRALS AND ASSISTANCE WITH LOW-COST MEDICATIONS. DURING THE FISCAL YEAR THERE WERE 20,473 ENCOUNTERS WITH 6,841 PATIENTS SERVED ORGANIZATION WIDE. UNINSURED PATIENTS ARE CHARGED ON A SLIDING FEE SCALE BASED ON INCOME LEVELS.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: DENTAL CARE - FIRST CARE CLINIC, INC. CONTINUED OPERATIONS IN A DENTAL CLINIC. DENTAL SERVICES INCLUDE: EXAMS, X-RAYS, RESTORATION(FILLINGS), EXTRACTIONS, CLEANINGS, CROWNS, BRIDGES AND ENDODONTIC(ROOT CANALS). UNINSURED PATIENTS ARE CHARGED ON A SLIDING FEE SCALE BASED ON INCOME LEVELS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: DIRECT CONTACT WITH LEGISLATORS OR A LEGISLATIVE BODY: THE CEO ATTENDED THE STATE LEGISLATIVE DAY. This was held virtually in 2022. $600 IS DEEMED TO BE THE ESTIMATE OF HIS TIME SPENT AT THE ACTIVITY.
OTHER LOBBYING ACTIVITIES: THE ORGANIZATION PAYS DUES TO THE NATIONAL ASSOCIATION OF COMMUNITY HEALTH CENTERS. A PORTION OF THESE DUES MAY BE ATTRIBUTABLE TO LOBBYING PURPOSES.

UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS: MANAGEMENT HAS EVALUATED THEIR INCOME TAX POSITIONS UNDER THE GUIDANCE INCLUDED IN ASC 740. BASED ON THEIR REVIEW, MANAGEMENT HAS NOT IDENTIFIED ANY MATERIAL UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS TO BE RECORDED OR DISCLOSED IN THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: REVIEW OF THE FORM 990: THE FORM 990 IS PREPARED BY AN INDEPENDENT ACCOUNTING FIRM BASED ON THE AUDITED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AND INFORMATION PROVIDED BY THE ACCOUNTING DEPARTMENT OF THE ORGANIZATION. PRIOR TO FILING, THE FORM IS REVIEWED BY THE CEO AND CFO OF THE ORGANIZATION AND PRESENTED TO THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS AT THEIR REGULAR MEETING.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: MONITORING COMPLIANCE WITH CONFLICT-OF-INTEREST POLICY: ALL KEY EMPLOYEES AND BOARD MEMBERS FILL OUT AND SIGN ANNUAL DISCLOSURES THAT REQUIRE THEM TO DOCUMENT ANY CONFLICT OF INTEREST. THESE FORMS ARE THEN REVIEWED BY THE ORGANIZATION'S COMPLIANCE OFFICER AND UPPER MANAGEMENT. COMPLIANCE WITH THIS POLICY IS MONITORED BY THE ORGANIZATION'S COMPLIANCE OFFICER. NO EMPLOYEE, OFFICER OR AGENT SHALL PARTICIPATE IN THE SELECTION, AWARD OR ADMINISTRATION OF A CONTRACT SUPPORTED BY FEDERAL FUNDS IF A REAL OR APPARENT CONFLICT OF INTEREST WOULD BE INVOLVED.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: CEO COMPENSATION REVIEW: THE COMPENSATION REVIEW WAS COMPLETED IN FY 2019. MEMBERS OF THE BOARD'S EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE PERFORMED THE REVIEW USING INFORMATION AVAILABLE FROM SALARY SURVEYS OF FEDERALLY QUALIFIED HEALTH CENTERS BOTH NATIONALLY AND REGIONALLY. THE PROCESS WAS DOCUMENTED IN THE BOARD MEETING MINUTES OF THE ORGANIZATION.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: DOCUMENT DISCLOSURE: THE ORGANIZATION'S GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY, AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ARE AVAILABLE TO BE VIEWED BY THE PUBLIC IN THE ORGANIZATION'S OFFICE UPON WRITTEN REQUEST.
